      "cause": "R2 has the 10.0.0.0/30 (link to R1) advertised in OSPF area 1 while R1 advertises the same 10.0.0.0 network in area 0. This area mismatch prevents an OSPF adjacency between R1 and R2, isolating R2 from R1 and preventing R1's LAN (192.168.0.0/24) from learning a correct route to 172.16.0.0/24 via R2.",
      "evidence": [
        "R1 OSPF networks (from R1 running-config): network 10.0.0.0 wildcard 0.0.0.3 area 0",
